race.comment: PARTY IT DOWN (5) was in the money first up at this track then had no luck at all when well-supported at Goulburn. Rates highly and will go close on the bounce. BLUE BAYOU (3)  has been in the market at her last couple of starts but hasn't made an impression. Missed a whisker the two prior at Moruya, and they read well for this. Better suited and can win on best figures. TOMMY FLYER (2) resumes for the Nick Olive yard and raced favourite his last two. Hasn't placed in the two fresh runs but has the ability and may be more forward this time around. PACIFIC MICK (4) wasn't too far away and Kembla Grange on debut and this is easier. Fitter and draws to advantage. Keep safe.
